-- TABLE-Qatar bank lending, M2 growth ease in March 
-- By Martin Dokoupil
-- Thu May 08, 2014 12:22PM EDT
-- None



May 8 (Reuters) - Money supply (M2) growth in Qatar slowed to 15.9 percent year-on-year at the end of March from 18.4 percent in the previous month, central bank data showed on Thursday.

Total bank credit in the OPEC member grew 14.5 percent on an annual basis in March, down from 17.0 percent in February, which was the fastest clip since May 2013. Non-resident deposits fell 25.8 percent on an annual basis and 1.1 percent month-on-month to 30.95 billion riyals ($8.5 billion), which is the lowest level since November 2013.